                            <comment id="13956464" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 12:35:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Did you start accessing your super column families from CQL on the 2.0 nodes before all nodes were upgraded to 2.0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13956470" author="hibou" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 12:47:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No, we have currently no code which use the CQL API, all is done via Thrift (through Hector).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13956553" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 14:27:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We indeed had a bug (2 in fact) when translating internal filters to thrift SC filters. Attaching a fix, and I&apos;ve pushed &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/commit/7f24091e5ba4220d58649cd7e49e5403630ea646&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;a dtest&lt;/a&gt; for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13957261" author="iamaleksey" created="Wed, 2 Apr 2014 02:14:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM. Attaching  a bikeshed version that reuses newFinish in sliceFilterToSC() and simplifies namesFilterToSC().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13957592" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 2 Apr 2014 12:30:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
